Other cast members, including Todd Tucker and Kandi Burruss were on hand as well, but wife Parks was MIA, like she has been for weeks as Nida prepares to go to prison for eight years.
He previously admitted to Radar that the couple were working on their “issues,” but spoke out again this week about the dire state of his marriage.
PHOTOS: Real Housewives, Real Scandals: 28 Of The Biggest Scandals To Hit The Bravo Franchise
Asked during an interview with Atlanta’s B100 radio station whether his marriage with Parks would survive his prison stint, Nida said, “I doubt it.”
“I mean, my wife didn’t even f***ing show up to my sentencing,” he continued. “I’m still salty about that.”
As Radar has reported, Nida and Parks were not seen together from April 4 until earlier this week, when they shot scenes for RHOA. 
